    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="585"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                <head>No. 586.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 216.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I forward herewith, for your information, the
                    inclosed copy of a note<note n="*" xml:id="d585fn1">For inclosure see document
                        287, <ref target="#pg_495">page 495</ref>.</note> of the 10th instant from
                    the British minister at this capital, in relation to the co-operation of Her
                    Majesty’s representative at Caracas with you, in addressing the Government of
                    Venezuela upon the subject of the custody of ships’ papers.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
